cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CSCW, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper examines the social networking practices of nonprofit organizations, specifically their use of Facebook as a stakeholder engagement tool. It focuses on the communication aspect of social media and how it affects public engagement. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also involves social media analysis, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, it discusses community-building practices, which is related to cs.CSCW (Computer-Supported Cooperative Work). The paper also touches on public engagement, which is relevant to cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
